text: Porte-de-Benauge is a commune. It is found in the region Nouvelle-Aquitaine in the Gironde department in the southwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Arbis (the seat) and Cantois.Arrêté préfectoral 28 September 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Gironde
title: Porte-de-Benauge
